# Adaptation Plan

## Intent
The patch factors out repeated job-killing logic into a static `broadcastKill` method in `TransportDistributedResultAction` that sends kill requests to all nodes except the local one, and uses it both when no root task is found and when a `DistributingConsumer` receives failures from all downstreams after sending data/failures, propagating the failure upwards via `completeExceptionally` to unblock upstream operations and prevent stuck distributed queries.

